title: Izzy Tector’s Website
text:
Hello! My name is Izzy Tector and I am a second year Environmental Studies major at UCSB from Washington State.

Education
BS in Environmental Studies (2021-present)
University of California, Santa Barbara


Experience
Restoration Intern (2023-present)
Helping Chris Berry at the Lagoon Island restoring native plants
Environmental Leadership Incubator Project (2022-present)
Participating in the Environmental Leadership Incubator and creating an educational campaign for environmental food labels
Sandwich Artist (2022)
Sandwich maker at Homegrown in Redmond, WA

title: About
text:
Eli Project
The ELI project I am currently working on has a website to teach UCSB students (or whoever might want to learn!) about environmental food labels. We hosted a workshop (seen in the picture!) and I helped create this website with my team!


CCBER Internship
I am currently interning for CCBER on campus and helping restore some of the lands that CCBER manages. It is a really exciting and fun thing to do because there’s a lot of adventure and learning! We recently went on a wild radish hunt, seen on the picture on the home page.
